"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebsite=self.webpackChunkwebsite||[]).push([[3735],{1275:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"memorare","title":"Memorare","category":"marian","type":"devotional","description":"A traditional prayer to the Virgin Mary asking for her intercession, expressing confidence in her maternal care","origin":"Attributed to St. Bernard of Clairvaux, popularized by St. Claude de la Colombi\xe8re","origin_date":"1090/1153","usage":"Recited in times of need, distress, or when seeking Mary\'s intercession and protection","feast_days":["all-marian-feasts","assumption","immaculate-conception"],"devotions":["marian-devotions","daily-prayers"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Memorare, o piissima Virgo Maria, non esse auditum a saeculo, quemquam ad tua currentem praesidia, tua implorantem auxilia, tua petentem suffragia, esse derelictum. Ego tali animatus confidentia, ad te, Virgo Virginum, Mater, curro, ad te venio, coram te gemens peccator assisto. Noli, Mater Verbi, verba mea despicere; sed audi propitia et exaudi. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin version attributed to St. Bernard of Clairvaux"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Remember, O most gracious Virgin Mary, that never was it known that anyone who fled to thy protection, implored thy help, or sought thy intercession was left unaided. Inspired by this confidence, I fly unto thee, O Virgin of virgins, my Mother; to thee do I come, before thee I stand, sinful and sorrowful. O Mother of the Word Incarnate, despise not my petitions, but in thy mercy hear and answer me. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic translation"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Acordaos, oh piados\xedsima Virgen Mar\xeda, que jam\xe1s se ha o\xeddo decir que ninguno de los que han acudido a vuestra protecci\xf3n, implorado vuestra asistencia y reclamado vuestro socorro, haya sido abandonado de vos. Animado por esta confianza, a vos acudo, oh Madre, Virgen de las v\xedrgenes, y gimiendo bajo el peso de mis pecados, me postro ante vos. Oh Madre del Verbo divino, no desech\xe9is mis s\xfaplicas, antes bien, escuchadlas y acogedlas benignamente. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Versi\xf3n cat\xf3lica espa\xf1ola tradicional"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Souvenez-vous, \xf4 tr\xe8s mis\xe9ricordieuse Vierge Marie, qu\'on n\'a jamais entendu dire qu\'aucun de ceux qui ont eu recours \xe0 votre protection, implor\xe9 votre assistance et r\xe9clam\xe9 votre secours, ait \xe9t\xe9 abandonn\xe9. Anim\xe9 d\'une pareille confiance, \xf4 Vierge des vierges, \xf4 ma M\xe8re, je cours vers vous, et g\xe9missant sous le poids de mes p\xe9ch\xe9s, je me prosterne \xe0 vos pieds. \xd4 M\xe8re du Verbe incarn\xe9, ne m\xe9prisez pas mes pri\xe8res, mais \xe9coutez-les favorablement et daignez les exaucer. Amen.","notes":"Version fran\xe7aise catholique traditionnelle"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Gedenke, o g\xfctigste Jungfrau Maria, es ist noch nie geh\xf6rt worden, dass jemand, der zu deinem Schutz seine Zuflucht nahm, deine Hilfe anrief und um deine F\xfcrsprache flehte, von dir verlassen worden sei. Von solchem Vertrauen beseelt, eile ich zu dir, o Jungfrau der Jungfrauen, meine Mutter; zu dir komme ich, vor dir stehe ich seufzend als S\xfcnder. O Mutter des ewigen Wortes, verschm\xe4he nicht meine Bitten, sondern h\xf6re mich gn\xe4dig an und erh\xf6re mich. Amen.","notes":"Deutsche katholische \xdcbersetzung"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Ricordati, o piissima Vergine Maria, che non si \xe8 mai sentito al mondo che alcuno abbia ricorso al tuo patrocinio, implorato il tuo aiuto, chiesto la tua protezione, e sia stato da te abbandonato. Animato da tale confidenza, a te ricorro, o Madre, Vergine delle vergini; a te vengo, e peccatore contrito mi prostro ai tuoi piedi. Non volere, o Madre del Verbo, disprezzare le mie preghiere, ma benigna ascoltale ed esaudiscile. Amen.","notes":"Versione italiana cattolica tradizionale"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Lembrai-vos, \xf3 pur\xedssima Virgem Maria, que jamais se ouviu dizer que algu\xe9m que tenha recorrido \xe0 vossa prote\xe7\xe3o, implorado a vossa assist\xeancia e solicitado o vosso patroc\xednio, fosse por v\xf3s desamparado. Animado desta confian\xe7a, a v\xf3s recorro, \xf3 M\xe3e, Virgem das virgens; a v\xf3s venho e, diante de v\xf3s me prostro, pecador contrito. N\xe3o desprezeis as minhas s\xfaplicas, \xf3 M\xe3e do Verbo divino, mas escutai-as prop\xedcia e dignai-vos atend\xea-las. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Vers\xe3o portuguesa cat\xf3lica tradicional"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"Wspomnij, o najmi\u0142osiersza Panno Maryjo, \u017ce nie s\u0142yszano od wiek\xf3w, aby ktokolwiek, uciekaj\u0105c si\u0119 pod Twoj\u0105 obron\u0119, wzywaj\u0105cy Twojej pomocy, b\u0142agaj\u0105cy o Twoje wstawiennictwo, zosta\u0142 opuszczony. Ja te\u017c, o\u017cywiony tak\u0105 ufno\u015bci\u0105, uciekam si\u0119 do Ciebie, o Panno nad pannami, o moja Matko; do Ciebie przychodz\u0119, przed Tob\u0105 staj\u0119, j\u0119cz\u0105c jako grzesznik. Nie gard\u017a, o Matko S\u0142owa Wcielonego, moimi s\u0142owami, ale \u0142askawie wys\u0142uchaj i spe\u0142nij. Amen.","notes":"Polska katolicka wersja tradycyjna"}}}')},5395:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"hail-holy-queen","title":"Hail Holy Queen (Salve Regina)","category":"marian","type":"liturgical","description":"A Marian antiphon expressing devotion to Mary as Queen of Heaven and Mother of Mercy","origin":"Traditionally attributed to Hermann of Reichenau, used in Compline during certain liturgical seasons","origin_date":"1013/1054","usage":"Recited at Compline, after the Rosary, and in various Marian devotions","feast_days":["assumption","queenship-of-mary","all-marian-feasts"],"devotions":["rosary","compline","marian-devotions"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Salve, Regina, Mater misericordiae, vita, dulcedo et spes nostra, salve. Ad te clamamus exsules filii Hevae, ad te suspiramus, gementes et flentes in hac lacrimarum valle. Eia, ergo, advocata nostra, illos tuos misericordes oculos ad nos converte. Et Jesum, benedictum fructum ventris tui, nobis post hoc exsilium ostende. O clemens, O pia, O dulcis Virgo Maria.","notes":"Traditional Latin antiphon attributed to Hermann of Reichenau"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Hail, holy Queen, Mother of mercy, our life, our sweetness, and our hope. To thee do we cry, poor banished children of Eve. To thee do we send up our sighs, mourning and weeping in this valley of tears. Turn then, most gracious advocate, thine eyes of mercy toward us. And after this our exile, show unto us the blessed fruit of thy womb, Jesus. O clement, O loving, O sweet Virgin Mary.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic translation"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Salve, Reina y Madre de misericordia, vida, dulzura y esperanza nuestra, Dios te salve. A ti clamamos los desterrados hijos de Eva, a ti suspiramos, gimiendo y llorando en este valle de l\xe1grimas. Ea, pues, Se\xf1ora, abogada nuestra, vuelve a nosotros esos tus ojos misericordiosos, y despu\xe9s de este destierro, mu\xe9stranos a Jes\xfas, fruto bendito de tu vientre. \xa1Oh clemente, oh piadosa, oh dulce Virgen Mar\xeda!","notes":"Versi\xf3n cat\xf3lica espa\xf1ola tradicional"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Salut, \xf4 Reine, M\xe8re de mis\xe9ricorde, notre vie, notre douceur et notre espoir, salut! Enfants d\'\xc8ve exil\xe9s, nous crions vers vous; vers vous nous soupirons, g\xe9missant et pleurant dans cette vall\xe9e de larmes. \xd4 vous donc, notre avocate, tournez vers nous vos regards mis\xe9ricordieux. Et apr\xe8s cet exil, montrez-nous J\xe9sus, le fruit b\xe9ni de vos entrailles. \xd4 cl\xe9mente, \xf4 mis\xe9ricordieuse, \xf4 douce Vierge Marie!","notes":"Version fran\xe7aise catholique traditionnelle"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Sei gegr\xfc\xdft, o K\xf6nigin, Mutter der Barmherzigkeit, unser Leben, unsere Wonne und unsere Hoffnung, sei gegr\xfc\xdft! Zu dir rufen wir verbannte Kinder Evas; zu dir seufzen wir, trauernd und weinend in diesem Tal der Tr\xe4nen. Wohlan denn, unsere F\xfcrsprecherin, wende deine barmherzigen Augen uns zu; und nach diesem Elend zeige uns Jesus, die gebenedeite Frucht deines Leibes. O g\xfctige, o milde, o s\xfc\xdfe Jungfrau Maria!","notes":"Deutsche katholische \xdcbersetzung"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Salve, Regina, Madre di misericordia, vita, dolcezza e speranza nostra, salve. A te ricorriamo, esuli figli di Eva; a te sospiriamo, gementi e piangenti in questa valle di lacrime. Ors\xf9 dunque, avvocata nostra, rivolgi a noi gli occhi tuoi misericordiosi. E mostraci, dopo questo esilio, Ges\xf9, il frutto benedetto del tuo seno. O clemente, o pia, o dolce Vergine Maria!","notes":"Versione italiana cattolica tradizionale"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Salve, Rainha, M\xe3e de miseric\xf3rdia, vida, do\xe7ura e esperan\xe7a nossa, salve! A v\xf3s bradamos, os degredados filhos de Eva. A v\xf3s suspiramos, gemendo e chorando neste vale de l\xe1grimas. Eia pois, advogada nossa, esses vossos olhos misericordiosos a n\xf3s volvei. E depois deste desterro, mostrai-nos Jesus, bendito fruto do vosso ventre. \xd3 clemente, \xf3 piedosa, \xf3 doce sempre Virgem Maria!","notes":"Vers\xe3o portuguesa cat\xf3lica tradicional"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"Witaj, Kr\xf3lowo, Matko mi\u0142osierdzia, \u017cycie, s\u0142odyczy i nadziejo nasza, witaj! Do Ciebie wo\u0142amy, wygnani synowie Ewy, do Ciebie wzdychamy, j\u0119cz\u0105c i p\u0142acz\u0105c w tej dolinie p\u0142aczu. Przeto, o Rzeczniczko nasza, oczy swoje mi\u0142osierne na nas zwr\xf3\u0107. A Jezusa, b\u0142ogos\u0142awiony owoc \u017cywota Twego, po tym wygnaniu nam oka\u017c. O \u0142askawa, o lito\u015bciwa, o s\u0142odka Panno Maryjo!","notes":"Polska katolicka wersja tradycyjna"}}}')},5654:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"hail-mary","title":"Hail Mary","category":"marian","type":"devotional","description":"A traditional Catholic prayer to the Virgin Mary, combining the angel Gabriel\'s greeting and Elizabeth\'s blessing","origin":"Based on Luke 1:28 (Angel Gabriel\'s greeting) and Luke 1:42 (Elizabeth\'s blessing), with traditional Catholic addition","origin_date":"1050/1150","usage":"Central prayer of the Rosary, daily Marian devotions, and Catholic worship","feast_days":["annunciation","visitation","all-marian-feasts"],"devotions":["rosary","angelus","marian-devotions"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Ave Maria, gratia plena, Dominus tecum. Benedicta tu in mulieribus, et benedictus fructus ventris tui, Iesus. Sancta Maria, Mater Dei, ora pro nobis peccatoribus, nunc et in hora mortis nostrae. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin version used in Catholic liturgy"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Hail Mary, full of grace, the Lord is with thee. Blessed art thou among women, and blessed is the fruit of thy womb, Jesus. Holy Mary, Mother of God, pray for us sinners, now and at the hour of our death. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic version"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Dios te salve, Mar\xeda, llena eres de gracia, el Se\xf1or es contigo. Bendita t\xfa eres entre todas las mujeres, y bendito es el fruto de tu vientre, Jes\xfas. Santa Mar\xeda, Madre de Dios, ruega por nosotros, pecadores, ahora y en la hora de nuestra muerte. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Standard Spanish Catholic version"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Je vous salue, Marie, pleine de gr\xe2ce, le Seigneur est avec vous. Vous \xeates b\xe9nie entre toutes les femmes, et J\xe9sus, le fruit de vos entrailles, est b\xe9ni. Sainte Marie, M\xe8re de Dieu, priez pour nous, pauvres p\xe9cheurs, maintenant et \xe0 l\'heure de notre mort. Amen.","notes":"French Catholic liturgical version"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Gegr\xfc\xdfet seist du, Maria, voll der Gnade, der Herr ist mit dir. Du bist gebenedeit unter den Frauen, und gebenedeit ist die Frucht deines Leibes, Jesus. Heilige Maria, Mutter Gottes, bitte f\xfcr uns S\xfcnder, jetzt und in der Stunde unseres Todes. Amen.","notes":"German Catholic liturgical version"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Ave, o Maria, piena di grazia, il Signore \xe8 con te. Tu sei benedetta fra le donne e benedetto \xe8 il frutto del tuo seno, Ges\xf9. Santa Maria, Madre di Dio, prega per noi peccatori, adesso e nell\'ora della nostra morte. Amen.","notes":"Italian Catholic liturgical version"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Ave Maria, cheia de gra\xe7a, o Senhor \xe9 convosco. Bendita sois v\xf3s entre as mulheres, e bendito \xe9 o fruto do vosso ventre, Jesus. Santa Maria, M\xe3e de Deus, rogai por n\xf3s, pecadores, agora e na hora da nossa morte. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Portuguese Catholic liturgical version"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"Zdrowa\u015b Maryjo, \u0142aski pe\u0142na, Pan z Tob\u0105. B\u0142ogos\u0142awiona jeste\u015b mi\u0119dzy niewiastami, i b\u0142ogos\u0142awiony owoc \u017cywota Twojego, Jezus. \u015awi\u0119ta Maryjo, Matko Bo\u017ca, m\xf3dl si\u0119 za nami grzesznymi, teraz i w godzin\u0119 \u015bmierci naszej. Amen.","notes":"Polish Catholic liturgical version"}}}')},6276:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"st-michael-prayer","title":"Prayer to St. Michael the Archangel","category":"petition","type":"devotional","description":"A prayer for protection against evil, invoking the intercession of St. Michael the Archangel","origin":"Composed by Pope Leo XIII after a vision, originally part of the Leonine Prayers","origin_date":"1886","usage":"Recited for spiritual protection, after Mass (historically), and in times of spiritual warfare","feast_days":["st-michael-archangel","all-saints"],"devotions":["daily-prayers","spiritual-warfare","protection-prayers"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Sancte Michael Archangele, defende nos in proelio, contra nequitiam et insidias diaboli esto praesidium. Imperet illi Deus, supplices deprecamur: tuque, Princeps militiae caelestis, Satanam aliosque spiritus malignos, qui ad perditionem animarum pervagantur in mundo, divina virtute, in infernum detrude. Amen.","notes":"Original Latin version composed by Pope Leo XIII"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Saint Michael the Archangel, defend us in battle, be our protection against the wickedness and snares of the devil. May God rebuke him, we humbly pray; and do thou, O Prince of the heavenly host, by the power of God, thrust into hell Satan and all the evil spirits who prowl about the world seeking the ruin of souls. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English translation"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"San Miguel Arc\xe1ngel, defi\xe9ndenos en la batalla, s\xe9 nuestro amparo contra la perversidad y asechanzas del demonio. Repr\xedmale Dios, suplicamos suplicantes, y t\xfa, Pr\xedncipe de la Milicia celestial, arroja al infierno con el divino poder a Satan\xe1s y a los otros esp\xedritus malignos que andan dispersos por el mundo para la perdici\xf3n de las almas. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Traducci\xf3n cat\xf3lica espa\xf1ola tradicional"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Saint Michel Archange, d\xe9fendez-nous dans le combat, soyez notre secours contre la m\xe9chancet\xe9 et les emb\xfbches du d\xe9mon. Que Dieu exerce sur lui son empire, nous vous en supplions; et vous, Prince de la milice c\xe9leste, repoussez en enfer, par la force divine, Satan et les autres esprits mauvais qui r\xf4dent dans le monde pour la perte des \xe2mes. Amen.","notes":"Version fran\xe7aise catholique traditionnelle"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Heiliger Erzengel Michael, verteidige uns im Kampfe, gegen die Bosheit und die Nachstellungen des Teufels sei unser Schutz. Gott gebiete ihm, so bitten wir flehentlich; und du, F\xfcrst der himmlischen Heerscharen, st\xfcrze den Satan und die anderen b\xf6sen Geister, die in der Welt umhergehen, um die Seelen zu verderben, durch die Kraft Gottes in die H\xf6lle. Amen.","notes":"Deutsche katholische \xdcbersetzung"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"San Michele Arcangelo, difendici nella battaglia, sii tu nostro sostegno contro la perversit\xe0 e le insidie del diavolo. Che Dio eserciti il suo dominio su di lui, te ne preghiamo supplichevoli; e tu, Principe della milizia celeste, ricaccia nell\'inferno satana e gli altri spiriti del male che si aggirano per il mondo per la perdizione delle anime. Amen.","notes":"Versione italiana cattolica tradizionale"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"S\xe3o Miguel Arcanjo, defendei-nos no combate, sede o nosso ref\xfagio contra a maldade e as ciladas do dem\xf4nio. Ordene-lhe Deus, assim o pedimos suplicantes; e v\xf3s, Pr\xedncipe da mil\xedcia celestial, pela virtude divina, precipitai no inferno a Satan\xe1s e aos outros esp\xedritos malignos que andam pelo mundo para perdi\xe7\xe3o das almas. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Vers\xe3o portuguesa cat\xf3lica tradicional"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"\u015awi\u0119ty Michale Archaniele, bro\u0144 nas w walce, b\u0105d\u017a nasz\u0105 ochron\u0105 przeciwko niegodziwo\u015bci i pu\u0142apkom diab\u0142a. Niech go B\xf3g ukr\xf3ci, pokornie prosimy; a ty, Ksi\u0105\u017c\u0119 Zast\u0119p\xf3w niebieskich, moc\u0105 Bo\u017c\u0105 str\u0105\u0107 do piek\u0142a szatana i innych z\u0142ych duch\xf3w, kt\xf3rzy kr\u0105\u017c\u0105 po \u015bwiecie na zgub\u0119 dusz. Amen.","notes":"Polska katolicka wersja tradycyjna"}}}')},8551:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"our-father","title":"Our Father","category":"christological","type":"scriptural","description":"The prayer taught by Jesus Christ to his disciples, also known as the Lord\'s Prayer","origin":"Gospel of Matthew 6:9-13 and Luke 11:2-4, taught by Jesus Christ","origin_date":"0030/0033","usage":"Central prayer of Christian worship, recited in Mass, Rosary, and daily prayers","feast_days":["all-liturgical-celebrations"],"devotions":["rosary","daily-prayers","mass"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Pater noster, qui es in caelis, sanctificetur nomen tuum. Adveniat regnum tuum. Fiat voluntas tua, sicut in caelo et in terra. Panem nostrum quotidianum da nobis hodie, et dimitte nobis debita nostra sicut et nos dimittimus debitoribus nostris. Et ne nos inducas in tentationem, sed libera nos a malo. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin version used in the Roman Catholic liturgy"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Our Father, who art in heaven, hallowed be thy name. Thy kingdom come, thy will be done, on earth as it is in heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our trespasses, as we forgive those who trespass against us. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English translation commonly used in Catholic prayer"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Padre nuestro, que est\xe1s en el cielo, santificado sea tu nombre. Venga a nosotros tu reino, h\xe1gase tu voluntad en la tierra como en el cielo. Danos hoy nuestro pan de cada d\xeda, perdona nuestras ofensas, como tambi\xe9n nosotros perdonamos a los que nos ofenden. No nos dejes caer en tentaci\xf3n, y l\xedbranos del mal. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Standard Spanish Catholic version"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Notre P\xe8re, qui es aux cieux, que ton nom soit sanctifi\xe9, que ton r\xe8gne vienne, que ta volont\xe9 soit faite sur la terre comme au ciel. Donne-nous aujourd\'hui notre pain de ce jour. Pardonne-nous nos offenses, comme nous pardonnons aussi \xe0 ceux qui nous ont offens\xe9s. Et ne nous laisse pas entrer en tentation, mais d\xe9livre-nous du Mal. Amen.","notes":"French Catholic liturgical version"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Vater unser im Himmel, geheiligt werde dein Name. Dein Reich komme. Dein Wille geschehe, wie im Himmel, so auf Erden. Unser t\xe4gliches Brot gib uns heute. Und vergib uns unsere Schuld, wie auch wir vergeben unsern Schuldigern. Und f\xfchre uns nicht in Versuchung, sondern erl\xf6se uns von dem B\xf6sen. Amen.","notes":"German Catholic liturgical version"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Padre nostro, che sei nei cieli, sia santificato il tuo nome, venga il tuo regno, sia fatta la tua volont\xe0, come in cielo cos\xec in terra. Dacci oggi il nostro pane quotidiano, e rimetti a noi i nostri debiti come anche noi li rimettiamo ai nostri debitori, e non abbandonarci alla tentazione, ma liberaci dal male. Amen.","notes":"Italian Catholic liturgical version"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Pai nosso, que estais nos c\xe9us, santificado seja o vosso nome. Venha a n\xf3s o vosso reino. Seja feita a vossa vontade, assim na terra como no c\xe9u. O p\xe3o nosso de cada dia dai-nos hoje. Perdoai-nos as nossas ofensas, assim como n\xf3s perdoamos a quem nos tem ofendido. E n\xe3o nos deixeis cair em tenta\xe7\xe3o, mas livrai-nos do mal. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Portuguese Catholic liturgical version"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"Ojcze nasz, kt\xf3ry\u015b jest w niebiesiech, \u015bwi\u0119\u0107 si\u0119 imi\u0119 Twoje, przyjd\u017a kr\xf3lestwo Twoje, b\u0105d\u017a wola Twoja jako w niebie tak i na ziemi. Chleba naszego powszedniego daj nam dzisiaj. I odpu\u015b\u0107 nam nasze winy, jako i my odpuszczamy naszym winowajcom. I nie w\xf3d\u017a nas na pokuszenie, ale nas zbaw ode z\u0142ego. Amen.","notes":"Polish Catholic liturgical version"}}}')},8850:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"act-of-contrition","title":"Act of Contrition","category":"petition","type":"penitential","description":"A prayer expressing sorrow for sins committed and firm purpose of amendment, commonly recited during confession","origin":"Traditional Catholic prayer developed for the sacrament of penance","origin_date":"~1400","usage":"Recited during the sacrament of confession, examination of conscience, and personal prayer","feast_days":["all-saints","sacred-heart"],"devotions":["confession","daily-prayers","examination-of-conscience"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Deus meus, ex toto corde paenitet me omnium meorum peccatorum, eaque detestor, quia peccando, non solum poenas a te iuste statutas promeritus sum, sed praesertim quia offendi te, summum bonum, et amore dignissimum. Ideo firmiter propono, adiuvante gratia tua, de cetero me non peccaturum peccandique occasiones proximas fugiturum. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin version used in confession"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"O my God, I am heartily sorry for having offended Thee, and I detest all my sins because I dread the loss of heaven and the pains of hell, but most of all because they offend Thee, my God, who art all good and deserving of all my love. I firmly resolve, with the help of Thy grace, to confess my sins, to do penance, and to amend my life. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic version commonly used in confession"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Dios m\xedo, me pesa de todo coraz\xf3n haber pecado, porque al pecar he merecido el castigo del infierno y, sobre todo, porque te he ofendido a ti, que eres tan bueno y que tanto me amas. Por eso, con tu gracia, propongo firmemente confesarme, hacer penitencia y no volver a pecar. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Versi\xf3n cat\xf3lica espa\xf1ola tradicional para la confesi\xf3n"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Mon Dieu, j\'ai un tr\xe8s grand regret de vous avoir offens\xe9, parce que vous \xeates infiniment bon, infiniment aimable, et que le p\xe9ch\xe9 vous d\xe9pla\xeet. Je prends la ferme r\xe9solution, avec le secours de votre sainte gr\xe2ce, de ne plus vous offenser et de faire p\xe9nitence. Amen.","notes":"Version fran\xe7aise catholique traditionnelle pour la confession"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Mein Gott, es reut mich von ganzem Herzen, dass ich ges\xfcndigt habe, weil ich dadurch die Strafe des Fegefeuers und der H\xf6lle verdient habe, aber vor allem, weil ich dich beleidigt habe, meinen Gott, der du unendlich gut bist und alle meine Liebe verdienst. Darum nehme ich mir fest vor, mit Hilfe deiner Gnade zu beichten, Bu\xdfe zu tun und mein Leben zu bessern. Amen.","notes":"Deutsche katholische Version f\xfcr die Beichte"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Mio Dio, mi pento e mi dolgo con tutto il cuore dei miei peccati, perch\xe9 peccando ho meritato i tuoi castighi e molto pi\xf9 perch\xe9 ho offeso te, infinitamente buono e degno di essere amato sopra ogni cosa. Propongo col tuo santo aiuto di non offenderti mai pi\xf9 e di fuggire le occasioni di peccato. Amen.","notes":"Versione italiana cattolica tradizionale per la confessione"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Meu Deus, eu me arrependo, de todo o cora\xe7\xe3o, de vos ter ofendido, porque pequei contra v\xf3s, que sois t\xe3o bom e digno de ser amado sobre todas as coisas, e assim mere\xe7o ser castigado por v\xf3s. Proponho, com a vossa santa gra\xe7a, nunca mais pecar e fugir das ocasi\xf5es de pecado. Meu Jesus, miseric\xf3rdia! Am\xe9m.","notes":"Vers\xe3o portuguesa cat\xf3lica tradicional para a confiss\xe3o"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"\u017ba\u0142uj\u0119 z ca\u0142ego serca, \u017ce zgrzeszy\u0142em, i wszystkie grzechy moje nienawidz\u0119, nie tylko dlatego, \u017ce przez nie zas\u0142u\u017cy\u0142em sobie na kary, kt\xf3re mi s\u0142usznie wyznaczy\u0142e\u015b, ale g\u0142\xf3wnie dlatego, \u017ce obrazi\u0142em Ciebie, najwy\u017csze dobro i najgodniejsze mi\u0142o\u015bci. Dlatego mocno postanawiam z pomoc\u0105 \u0142aski Twojej wi\u0119cej ju\u017c nie grzeszy\u0107 i unika\u0107 okazji do grzechu. Amen.","notes":"Polska katolicka wersja tradycyjna dla spowiedzi"}}}')},9281:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"glory-be","title":"Glory Be","category":"praise","type":"doxology","description":"A short hymn of praise to the Trinity, also known as the Gloria Patri or Lesser Doxology","origin":"Ancient Christian doxology, developed in early centuries of the Church","origin_date":"~0200","usage":"Recited after psalms, decades of the Rosary, and various prayers as praise to the Trinity","feast_days":["trinity-sunday","all-liturgical-celebrations"],"devotions":["rosary","divine-office","daily-prayers"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"Gloria Patri, et Filio, et Spiritui Sancto. Sicut erat in principio, et nunc, et semper, et in saecula saeculorum. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin doxology used in liturgy"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit. As it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be, world without end. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic version"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"Gloria al Padre, y al Hijo, y al Esp\xedritu Santo. Como era en el principio, ahora y siempre, por los siglos de los siglos. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Standard Spanish Catholic version"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"Gloire au P\xe8re, et au Fils, et au Saint-Esprit. Comme il \xe9tait au commencement, maintenant et toujours, pour les si\xe8cles des si\xe8cles. Amen.","notes":"French Catholic liturgical version"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"Ehre sei dem Vater und dem Sohn und dem Heiligen Geist. Wie es war im Anfang, so auch jetzt und allezeit und in Ewigkeit. Amen.","notes":"German Catholic liturgical version"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"Gloria al Padre e al Figlio e allo Spirito Santo. Come era nel principio, e ora e sempre nei secoli dei secoli. Amen.","notes":"Italian Catholic liturgical version"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"Gl\xf3ria ao Pai, e ao Filho, e ao Esp\xedrito Santo. Como era no princ\xedpio, agora e sempre, pelos s\xe9culos dos s\xe9culos. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Portuguese Catholic liturgical version"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"Chwa\u0142a Ojcu i Synowi, i Duchowi \u015awi\u0119temu. Jak by\u0142a na pocz\u0105tku, teraz i zawsze, i na wieki wiek\xf3w. Amen.","notes":"Polish Catholic liturgical version"}}}')},9446:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"id":"angelus","title":"The Angelus","category":"marian","type":"devotional","description":"A traditional Marian devotion commemorating the Annunciation, recited three times daily","origin":"Developed from the practice of reciting Hail Marys at the sound of church bells","origin_date":"1200/1300","usage":"Recited at 6 AM, 12 PM, and 6 PM daily, traditionally at the sound of church bells","feast_days":["annunciation","all-marian-feasts"],"devotions":["daily-prayers","marian-devotions"],"created_date":"2025-07-14","last_modified":"2025-07-14"},"translations":{"la":{"language":"Latin","text":"V. Angelus Domini nuntiavit Mariae.\\nR. Et concepit de Spiritu Sancto.\\n\\nAve Maria, gratia plena, Dominus tecum. Benedicta tu in mulieribus, et benedictus fructus ventris tui, Iesus. Sancta Maria, Mater Dei, ora pro nobis peccatoribus, nunc et in hora mortis nostrae. Amen.\\n\\nV. Ecce ancilla Domini.\\nR. Fiat mihi secundum verbum tuum.\\n\\nAve Maria...\\n\\nV. Et Verbum caro factum est.\\nR. Et habitavit in nobis.\\n\\nAve Maria...\\n\\nV. Ora pro nobis, sancta Dei Genetrix.\\nR. Ut digni efficiamur promissionibus Christi.\\n\\nOremus: Gratiam tuam, quaesumus, Domine, mentibus nostris infunde; ut qui, Angelo nuntiante, Christi Filii tui incarnationem cognovimus, per passionem eius et crucem ad resurrectionis gloriam perducamur. Per eundem Christum Dominum nostrum. Amen.","notes":"Traditional Latin version with versicles and responses"},"en":{"language":"English","text":"V. The Angel of the Lord declared unto Mary.\\nR. And she conceived of the Holy Spirit.\\n\\nHail Mary, full of grace, the Lord is with thee. Blessed art thou among women, and blessed is the fruit of thy womb, Jesus. Holy Mary, Mother of God, pray for us sinners, now and at the hour of our death. Amen.\\n\\nV. Behold the handmaid of the Lord.\\nR. Be it done unto me according to thy word.\\n\\nHail Mary...\\n\\nV. And the Word was made flesh.\\nR. And dwelt among us.\\n\\nHail Mary...\\n\\nV. Pray for us, O holy Mother of God.\\nR. That we may be made worthy of the promises of Christ.\\n\\nLet us pray: Pour forth, we beseech Thee, O Lord, Thy grace into our hearts; that we, to whom the incarnation of Christ, Thy Son, was made known by the message of an angel, may by His passion and cross be brought to the glory of His resurrection. Through the same Christ our Lord. Amen.","notes":"Traditional English Catholic version with versicles and responses"},"es":{"language":"Spanish","text":"V. El \xc1ngel del Se\xf1or anunci\xf3 a Mar\xeda.\\nR. Y concibi\xf3 por obra del Esp\xedritu Santo.\\n\\nDios te salve, Mar\xeda, llena eres de gracia, el Se\xf1or es contigo. Bendita t\xfa eres entre todas las mujeres, y bendito es el fruto de tu vientre, Jes\xfas. Santa Mar\xeda, Madre de Dios, ruega por nosotros, pecadores, ahora y en la hora de nuestra muerte. Am\xe9n.\\n\\nV. He aqu\xed la esclava del Se\xf1or.\\nR. H\xe1gase en m\xed seg\xfan tu palabra.\\n\\nDios te salve, Mar\xeda...\\n\\nV. Y el Verbo se hizo carne.\\nR. Y habit\xf3 entre nosotros.\\n\\nDios te salve, Mar\xeda...\\n\\nV. Ruega por nosotros, Santa Madre de Dios.\\nR. Para que seamos dignos de las promesas de Cristo.\\n\\nOremos: Infunde, Se\xf1or, tu gracia en nuestros corazones, para que los que hemos conocido, por el anuncio del \xe1ngel, la encarnaci\xf3n de tu Hijo Jesucristo, por su pasi\xf3n y cruz seamos llevados a la gloria de su resurrecci\xf3n. Por el mismo Cristo nuestro Se\xf1or. Am\xe9n.","notes":"Versi\xf3n cat\xf3lica espa\xf1ola tradicional con vers\xedculos y respuestas"},"fr":{"language":"French","text":"V. L\'Ange du Seigneur porta l\'annonce \xe0 Marie.\\nR. Et elle con\xe7ut du Saint-Esprit.\\n\\nJe vous salue, Marie, pleine de gr\xe2ce, le Seigneur est avec vous. Vous \xeates b\xe9nie entre toutes les femmes, et J\xe9sus, le fruit de vos entrailles, est b\xe9ni. Sainte Marie, M\xe8re de Dieu, priez pour nous, pauvres p\xe9cheurs, maintenant et \xe0 l\'heure de notre mort. Amen.\\n\\nV. Voici la servante du Seigneur.\\nR. Qu\'il me soit fait selon votre parole.\\n\\nJe vous salue, Marie...\\n\\nV. Et le Verbe s\'est fait chair.\\nR. Et il a habit\xe9 parmi nous.\\n\\nJe vous salue, Marie...\\n\\nV. Priez pour nous, sainte M\xe8re de Dieu.\\nR. Afin que nous soyons rendus dignes des promesses du Christ.\\n\\nPrions: R\xe9pandez, Seigneur, votre gr\xe2ce dans nos c\u0153urs, afin que nous qui avons connu par l\'annonce de l\'ange l\'incarnation de votre Fils J\xe9sus-Christ, nous soyons conduits par sa passion et sa croix \xe0 la gloire de sa r\xe9surrection. Par le m\xeame J\xe9sus-Christ notre Seigneur. Amen.","notes":"Version fran\xe7aise catholique traditionnelle avec versets et r\xe9pons"},"de":{"language":"German","text":"V. Der Engel des Herrn brachte Maria die Botschaft.\\nR. Und sie empfing vom Heiligen Geist.\\n\\nGegr\xfc\xdfet seist du, Maria, voll der Gnade, der Herr ist mit dir. Du bist gebenedeit unter den Frauen, und gebenedeit ist die Frucht deines Leibes, Jesus. Heilige Maria, Mutter Gottes, bitte f\xfcr uns S\xfcnder, jetzt und in der Stunde unseres Todes. Amen.\\n\\nV. Siehe, ich bin die Magd des Herrn.\\nR. Mir geschehe nach deinem Wort.\\n\\nGegr\xfc\xdfet seist du, Maria...\\n\\nV. Und das Wort ist Fleisch geworden.\\nR. Und hat unter uns gewohnt.\\n\\nGegr\xfc\xdfet seist du, Maria...\\n\\nV. Bitte f\xfcr uns, heilige Gottesmutter.\\nR. Auf dass wir w\xfcrdig werden der Verhei\xdfungen Christi.\\n\\nLasset uns beten: Allm\xe4chtiger Gott, gie\xdfe deine Gnade in unsere Herzen ein, damit wir, die wir durch die Botschaft des Engels die Menschwerdung deines Sohnes Jesus Christus erkannt haben, durch sein Leiden und Kreuz zur Herrlichkeit seiner Auferstehung gef\xfchrt werden. Durch denselben Christus, unseren Herrn. Amen.","notes":"Deutsche katholische liturgische Version mit Versen und Antworten"},"it":{"language":"Italian","text":"V. L\'Angelo del Signore port\xf2 l\'annuncio a Maria.\\nR. Ed essa concep\xec per opera dello Spirito Santo.\\n\\nAve, o Maria, piena di grazia, il Signore \xe8 con te. Tu sei benedetta fra le donne e benedetto \xe8 il frutto del tuo seno, Ges\xf9. Santa Maria, Madre di Dio, prega per noi peccatori, adesso e nell\'ora della nostra morte. Amen.\\n\\nV. Ecco la serva del Signore.\\nR. Avvenga per me secondo la tua parola.\\n\\nAve, o Maria...\\n\\nV. E il Verbo si fece carne.\\nR. E venne ad abitare in mezzo a noi.\\n\\nAve, o Maria...\\n\\nV. Prega per noi, santa Madre di Dio.\\nR. Perch\xe9 siamo resi degni delle promesse di Cristo.\\n\\nPreghiamo: Infondi nel nostro spirito la tua grazia, o Signore; tu che nell\'annuncio dell\'Angelo ci hai rivelato l\'incarnazione del tuo Figlio, per la sua passione e la sua croce guidaci alla gloria della risurrezione. Per lo stesso Cristo nostro Signore. Amen.","notes":"Versione italiana cattolica liturgica con versetti e risposte"},"pt":{"language":"Portuguese","text":"V. O Anjo do Senhor anunciou a Maria.\\nR. E Ela concebeu do Esp\xedrito Santo.\\n\\nAve Maria, cheia de gra\xe7a, o Senhor \xe9 convosco. Bendita sois v\xf3s entre as mulheres, e bendito \xe9 o fruto do vosso ventre, Jesus. Santa Maria, M\xe3e de Deus, rogai por n\xf3s, pecadores, agora e na hora da nossa morte. Am\xe9m.\\n\\nV. Eis aqui a serva do Senhor.\\nR. Fa\xe7a-se em mim segundo a vossa palavra.\\n\\nAve Maria...\\n\\nV. E o Verbo se fez carne.\\nR. E habitou entre n\xf3s.\\n\\nAve Maria...\\n\\nV. Rogai por n\xf3s, santa M\xe3e de Deus.\\nR. Para que sejamos dignos das promessas de Cristo.\\n\\nOremos: Infundi, Senhor, a vossa gra\xe7a em nossos cora\xe7\xf5es, para que n\xf3s, que pela anuncia\xe7\xe3o do Anjo conhecemos a encarna\xe7\xe3o de vosso Filho Jesus Cristo, por sua paix\xe3o e cruz sejamos conduzidos \xe0 gl\xf3ria da ressurrei\xe7\xe3o. Pelo mesmo Cristo nosso Senhor. Am\xe9m.","notes":"Vers\xe3o portuguesa cat\xf3lica lit\xfargica com vers\xedculos e respostas"},"pl":{"language":"Polish","text":"V. Anio\u0142 Pa\u0144ski zwiastowa\u0142 Pannie Maryi.\\nR. I pocz\u0119\u0142a z Ducha \u015awi\u0119tego.\\n\\nZdrowa\u015b Maryjo, \u0142aski pe\u0142na, Pan z Tob\u0105. B\u0142ogos\u0142awiona jeste\u015b mi\u0119dzy niewiastami, i b\u0142ogos\u0142awiony owoc \u017cywota Twojego, Jezus. \u015awi\u0119ta Maryjo, Matko Bo\u017ca, m\xf3dl si\u0119 za nami grzesznymi, teraz i w godzin\u0119 \u015bmierci naszej. Amen.\\n\\nV. Oto ja s\u0142u\u017cebnica Pa\u0144ska.\\nR. Niech mi si\u0119 stanie wed\u0142ug s\u0142owa Twego.\\n\\nZdrowa\u015b Maryjo...\\n\\nV. A S\u0142owo sta\u0142o si\u0119 cia\u0142em.\\nR. I zamieszka\u0142o mi\u0119dzy nami.\\n\\nZdrowa\u015b Maryjo...\\n\\nV. M\xf3dl si\u0119 za nami, \u015bwi\u0119ta Bo\u017ca Rodzicielko.\\nR. Aby\u015bmy si\u0119 stali godnymi obietnic Chrystusowych.\\n\\nM\xf3dlmy si\u0119: Wszechmog\u0105cy Bo\u017ce, wlej \u0142ask\u0119 Twoj\u0105 w serca nasze, aby\u015bmy, kt\xf3rzy przez zwiastowanie Anio\u0142a poznali\u015bmy wcielenie Chrystusa, Syna Twojego, przez Jego m\u0119k\u0119 i krzy\u017c zostali doprowadzeni do chwa\u0142y zmartwychwstania. Przez tego\u017c Chrystusa, Pana naszego. Amen.","notes":"Polska katolicka wersja liturgiczna z wersetami i odpowiedziami"}}}')}}]);